<br>
See below for some recommendations for upgrading gear, but your gear now is adequate for orc hunting in CC. I might be more advisable to save your money and build a bigger wallet, as you will need better resist gear.<br>
<br>
Cheap upgrade suggestions:<br>
<br>
Gear: Situation, The monk wants to upgrade gear with only 800pp. All of these recommendations are designed to stay within your budget.<br>
<br>
Arms, wrists:<br>
Spore covered sleeves and two spore covered bracers, should take about one hour in NL to get all three. Bank the shackle and throw Wus away. Cost, Free, only takes a bit of patience crushing green fungoids in the Netherbian lair. Kill any fungoid other then the sporelings.<br>
<br>
Neck:<br>
Spider fur collar: Cost, goes for about 300 on Ayonae Ro. (Not sure if this really should be obtained). <br>
<br>
Head:<br>
Get rid of the Executioner's Hood and get a Lumberjack Cap. Surprising huh? 10AC and 3 str, wt1.5. Wt sucks but you can handle it. Goes for about 50pp if not free.<br>
<br>
Ears:<br>
Replace the Cougar with an orc fang? Hard to say, but all the stats on the cougar don't really help you and the orc fang has 15hp. You can get an orc fang for 50pp.<br>
<br>
Hands:<br>
Another shocker, Iksar scaled gloves, heavy yes, but 10ac, with hp and str rolled in, and they are very cheap, say 50pp. You can wear them and still make weight.<br>
<br>
So that leaves us about 350pp, 650pp if you don't replace the chipper velium.<br>
<br>
Your weapons. legs,feet,waist, back and chest are fine, I would recommend replacing the wus shoulder pads, only problem is, with what. Acrylia reinforced or studded would be the answer, but that runs about 800-1000pp on Ayonae maybe less.<br>
<br>
You may be able to get an acrylia reinforced mantle, for 650pp or less, if so, do it and keep the amulet, if not then get the spider fur and live with the Wus for a while.<br>
<br>
All these suggestions will increase your AC and HPs,which will allow you to live longer and kill more critters. <p><BR> 

